I"ı<p>Hard coded strings are annoying,<br />In XAML, we have a lot of cases of hard coded strings.<br /><br />Here is a simple way of implementing static naming class, and use it instead of hard coded strings.<br /><br />Suppose this is my xaml:<br /><br />&lt;pre class="brush: csharp;"&gt;&lt;Window x:Class=â€How.MainWindowâ€<br />        xmlns=â€http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentationâ€<br />        xmlns:x=â€http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xamlâ€<br />        xmlns:local=â€clr-namespace:Howâ€<br />        Title=â€MainWindowâ€ Height=â€350â€ Width=â€525â€&gt;<br />    &lt;Window.Resources&gt;<br />        &lt;Style TargetType=â€{x:Type Button}â€ x:Key=â€LazyGuyMeaninglessNameâ€&gt;<br />            &lt;Setter Property=â€Marginâ€ Value=â€30â€/&gt;<br />            &lt;Setter Property=â€Heightâ€ Value=â€30â€/&gt;<br />            &lt;Setter Property=â€Widthâ€ Value=â€200â€/&gt;<br />        &lt;/Style&gt;<br />    &lt;/Window.Resources&gt;<br />    &lt;StackPanel&gt;<br />            &lt;Button Click=â€Button_Clickâ€&gt;Click me to activate my style&lt;/Button&gt;<br />        &lt;Button Style=â€{DynamicResource LazyGuyMeaninglessName}â€/&gt;<br />    &lt;/StackPanel&gt;<br />&lt;/Window&gt;<br /><br />&lt;/pre&gt;<br />This is code behind:<br /><br />&lt;pre class="brush: csharp;"&gt;private void Button_Click(object sender, RoutedEventArgs e)<br />{<br />  var button = sender as Button;<br />  if (button != null)<br />  {<br />    button.Style = (Style)this.FindResource(â€œLazyGuyMeaninglessNameWithMistakeâ€);<br />  }<br />}<br />&lt;/pre&gt;<br />I have a mistake in my code behind, and the program will crash, not so fun, and not simple to test this kind of stuff.<br /><br />There is a very simple solution, Lets define this class:<br /><br />&lt;pre class="brush: csharp;"&gt;public static class StyleNames<br />{<br />  public static string ButtonStyleName = â€œSome Hard To write style nameâ€;<br />}<br />&lt;/pre&gt;<br />The benefits